  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Before archaeologists excavate, they begin with a pedestrian survey. This
    is the first look at a site before even marking out where you are planning to
    dig. The goal is to get an idea of where surface features are located, document
    surface artifacts, and orient yourself with your team within a site.


    The
    traditional method for a pedestrian survey uses transect lines. Team members
    will line up about three or four meters apart along the edge of the site or area
    you are focusing on. Slowly, the team will walk the length of the site and scan
    the ground for any surface artifacts or features and record them properly. Due
    to the singleplayer aspect of this experience, we accomplish this with drone
    work. Please click on the drone to begin the pedestrian survey, or walk the site
    and record information about surface artifacts. There are 6 in total that need
    to be recorded before excavation can begin!'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
